sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT player_id) AS total_players_scored
FROM player_stats
WHERE points > 0;

SELECT game_id, arena_name
FROM game_arenas
WHERE arena_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(arena_id) 
FROM arenas 
WHERE capacity > 18000;

SELECT COUNT(game_id) AS total_games
FROM games
WHERE season = (SELECT MAX(season) FROM games);

external_knowledge:
- "performance of each team shine" refers to the calculated metric of points per game duration;
- "unique duration of each game" refers to the varying lengths of different games;
- "points scored per minute of game play" is the result of the formula (points * game_duration) / sum(game_duration) for each team.

- "Team value" refers to the estimated financial worth of a team;
- "Average team value per game" is calculated by dividing the team's total value by the number of games played by that team;
- "Arenas" are the venues where games are held;
- The query focuses on the financial significance of the arenas based on the teams that play there.

- The comprehensive score is calculated as the sum of points, rebounds, assists, steals, and blocks minus turnovers;
- The average performance is the mean of the comprehensive scores across all games for each team;
- The top 5 teams are those with the highest average comprehensive scores.

- "shining brighter than the average star" refers to teams whose average points per game are greater than the overall average points scored across all games;
- "dazzling feats" refers to the games played by these teams;
- "grand arena of competition" refers to the different arenas where the games are played.
